AB  - The demand for bandwidth in networks is increasing at a tremendous rate. Traffic growth has significant effects in all parts of the network all the way from access to the core. The Internet transport infrastructure is moving toward a model of high-speed routers interconnected by intelligent optical core networks. Optical networks and communication systems, having enormous transmission capacity and bandwidth, are being exploited to obtain a quantum leap in communication bandwidth. In IP over WDM networks there is the routing and wavelength assignment (RWA) problem − the whole problem of routing in a WDM network with proper allocation of a minimum number of wavelengths. Therefore the reliability problem in the optical network is a significant issue. For increasing the reliability of the network technologies of protection and restoration of the network have been recently introduced. This article summarizes the present state of the technologies and addresses the fault localization and fault protection.
ER  -

