AB  - A quantum wire-dot structure has been realized by growth of a zigzag pattern with sidewalls alternating misaligned by + or - 30°. Such structures of interest both for fundamental studies of the interaction between quasi-one- and quasi-zero-dimensionally confined carriers and for device applications. This paper reports on the first low temperature near-field luminescence investigation of this novel coupled wire-dot structure, allowing the assignment of different optical transition energies to different spatial areas of the sample and demonstrating carrier transport along the quantum wire into the dot.
