AB  - The proceedings contain 48 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Metaheuristics. The topics include: Neural Architecture Search Using Differential Evolution in MAML Framework for Few-Shot Classification Problems; neural Architecture Search Using Metaheuristics for Automated Cell Segmentation; analytical Methods to Separately Evaluate Convergence and Diversity for Multi-objective Optimization; how a Different Ant Behavior Affects on the Performance of the Whole Colony; evaluating the Effects of Chaos in Variable Neighbourhood Search; investigating Fractal Decomposition Based Algorithm on Low-Dimensional Continuous Optimization Problems; a Comparative Analysis of Different Multilevel Approaches for Community Detection; tchebycheff Fractal Decomposition Algorithm for Bi-objective Optimization Problems; local Search for Integrated Predictive Maintenance and Scheduling in Flow-Shop; A BRKGA with Implicit Path-Relinking for the Vehicle Routing Problem with Occasional Drivers and Time Windows; an Investigation of Hyper-Heuristic Approaches for Teeth Scheduling; a Mixed-Integer Programming Formulation and Heuristics for an Integrated Production Planning and Scheduling Problem; construct, Merge, Solve and Adapt Applied to the Maximum Disjoint Dominating Sets Problem; fixed Set Search Applied to the Territory Design Problem; the P-Next Center Problem with Capacity and Coverage Radius Constraints: Model and Heuristics; automatic Configuration of Metaheuristics for Solving the Quadratic Three-Dimensional Assignment Problem Using Irace; hyper-parameter Optimization Using Continuation Algorithms; selecting the Parameters of an Evolutionary Algorithm for the Generation of Phenotypically Accurate Fractal Patterns; addressing Sustainability in Precision Agriculture via Multi-Objective Factored Evolutionary Algorithms; modeling and Solving the K-Track Assignment Problem; Metaheuristic Algorithms for UAV Trajectory Optimization in Mobile Networks; instance Space Analysis for the Generalized Assignment Problem; decision Support for Agri-Food Supply Chains in the E-Commerce Era: The Inbound Inventory Routing Problem with Perishable Products; a Multi-objective Biased Random-Key Genetic Algorithm for the Siting of Emergency Vehicles; simulated Annealing for a Complex Industrial Scheduling Problem; a Matheuristic for Multi-Depot Multi-Trip Vehicle Routing Problems; Comparing QUBO Models of the Magic Square Problem for Quantum Annealing; self-adaptive Publish/Subscribe Network Design; variable Neighborhood Descent for Software Quality Optimization.
