AU  - Zhang, Bo
AU  - Manger, M. F.
AU  - Batke, E.
TI  - Comment on “Magneto Infrared Absorption in High Electron Density GaAs Quantum Wells
LA  - eng
JF  - Physical Review Letters
VL  - 89
IS  - 3
PY  - 2002
SN  - 00319007, 10797114
PB  - AMERICAN PHYSICAL SOC
DO  - 10.1103/PhysRevLett.89.039703
AB  - In a recent Letter (ibid. vol.86, p.336, (2001)), Poulter et al. studied cyclotron resonance (CR) of high density and high mobility electron space-charge layers in thin GaAs quantum wells in Faraday geometry at frequencies covering the GaAs reststrahlen regime. No coupling of the CR to the bulk longitudinal-optical (LO) phonon was observed, and from weak shifts of the CR position and a simultaneously observed enhanced line broadening occurring close to the transverse-optical (TO) phonon frequency they deduced that the CR instead couples to a collective magnetoplasmon-phonon mode. We argue that the evidence for such a coupling is not convincing and criticize that the collective charge-density excitations of the quasi-two-dimensional electron systems (Q2DES) were discussed with reference to a model appropriate only for bulk systems. Such an approach even being considered as tentative cannot be justified since the collective modes of Q2DES and the bulk differ significantly. Poulter et al. reply and acknowledge the criticism and agree with Zhang et al. that the "3D-like" approach to describe the collective magnetoplasmon-phonon mode might indeed be too simplistic, particularly in the case of narrow quantum wells used in the experiments. It is, however, their opinion that the main experimental finding reported in the original work cannot be explained within the framework of current theory and the correct assignment for the observed interaction is far from trivial.
ER  -

