was found that the pattern of bands in NIR spectra of deuterated methanols
can be used for identification of isotopically equalized forms. Calculations
of NIR spectra of all possible forms of CXXXOX (X = H, D) molecules
demonstrated that the isotopic contamination can be identified due
to a coexistence of bands specific to OH and OD groups. Also, bands
from partially deuterated methyl groups can be distinguished in NIR
