AB  - The following topics are dealt with: above and below Wannier threshold ionization; quasi-atoms, super-atoms and quantum confinement; small-angle electron scattering: guiding measurements; single and multiple ionization of atoms by electron impact; laser cooling, evaporative cooling and Bose-Einstein condensation; inner shell ionisation with low velocity heavy ions; multiphoton strong-field physics; hyperfine quenching effects on the 3P02 level in He-like vanadium; multidimensional SSQM formalism application to He atom; energetic photoionization of neutral and ionic metal clusters; line strengths and line shapes of zero-phonon absorption features solid hydrogen; physics of positronium acceptor complex formation reactions; channeling radiation from relativistic electrons and positrons; isotope shifts in UV lines of dysprosium: confirmation and new assignments of 4f9d6s6p, 4f96s26p configurations to energy levels of Dy I angular dependence of scattering differential cross sections in double photon Compton scattering; positronium formation in helium with electron correlation effect; three-body recombination at low temperature - a field theoretic approach; single photo-ionization of He - a QED approach; normal coordinate analysis of deuterated benzonitriles and some pyridines; time reversal symmetry breaking superconducting states in cuprates; high resolution emission spectroscopy of rare and radioactive isotopes; rovibrational matrix elements of multipole moments of heavier isotopomers of molecular hydrogen; intensity and spectral distribution of 662 keV gamma rays Compton scattered from bound electrons of tin; electron impact ionization of multiply charged ion: a BE study; high resolution studies of A3π0-X1Σ+ band system of InCl; transport properties of gas mixtures; relativistic calculations of positron scattering from xenon (Xe) atom; time-dependent changes in the charge-transfer spectra of ferrocene in halocarbon solvents after photoexcitation; superelastic electron scattering from potassium atoms millimeter and submillimeter wave spectral studies of 13CD2F2; high resolution spectroscopic. studies of methyl acetylene: analysis of ν6 band of CD3CCH; design and fabrication of TOF spectrometer and a 45°-parallel plate electrostatic analyzer; two-photon excitation using L2 technique; computerized electronic locking system for diode laser frequency locking by saturated absorption spectroscopy of cesium; photoionization of noble gas atoms; laser cooling and trapping of cesium atoms in magneto-optical trap; infrared activity of "symmetry-forbidden" overtone bands of CO2 induced by asymmetric isotopic substitution; synchronization in chaotic jerk dynamical systems; incoherent scattering functions of some medium and heavy elements at 4.808 A-1 photon momentum transfer; two-photon ionization using pseudostate summation technique; time evolution of SERS of a-bithiophene and a-terthiophene adsorbed on Ag-sols; theoretical total cross sections of e-H2O collisions in water, ice and dimer forms; ionized helium induced ionization of atomic hydrogen; correlation effects on peptide molecules; elastic scattering of electrons from methane molecules.
